The paper is about using deep convolutional networks for visual recognition tasks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques for feature extraction and transfer learning, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of neural networks for optimization (cs.NE) and the release of an open-source implementation for experimentation (cs.MM).
